      </span>
				<p>The context for verse 18 is verse 19: &ldquo;For, behold, the beasts of the field and the fowls of the air &hellip; [are] ordained for the use of man for food.&rdquo; [<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/49.19?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 49:19</a>.]  Section 49 was specifically directed to members of the United Society of Believers in Christ&rsquo;s Second Appearing (the Shakers) to correct some of their erroneous doctrines. One of their beliefs was not to eat flesh-meat or fish.</p>
